A beautiful evening of wonderful jazz music! Truly a blessing! We were on a Harlem jazz tour and our tour guide, Joseph Cohen suggested we check out this Sunday evening tradition. It was his first time attending also and he really took a chance on bringing us to something that he himself wasn't familiar with. But man, did he really knock it out of the park with this one!!! originalText.text: A beautiful, wonderful experience. Light refreshments were served and the performance was free, though a tip bucket for the performers does go around, so bring cash. I was truly blown away by the talent and love present in the room. Thank you to Marjorie and the performers for allowing me to experience such a beautiful moment. 100% recommend if you're looking for some good jazz.

originalText.text: Honestly this was one of the highlights of our trip to New York. We wanted to see some jazz while we were in the Big Apple and we were not disappointed. You ring the bell for the apartment block, they buzz you through, and then shortly before the start time the indubitably classy Miss Eliot lets you into her home. She was a very gracious host- it wasn‚Äôt just that she was outstanding at playing piano (as were all the other performers), or the cereal bars and fig juice handed out during the performance, but the fact she seemed truly honoured that we had come to watch her play, whereas in fact the honour was all ours. When we come back to New York this will be top of our list! (And yes, it is FREE- mad to believe- but donations are appreciated.)
